The paper deals with the decidability of reachability for dynamic parametric processes, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of pushdown systems and higher-order pushdown systems suggests a connection to formal language theory (cs.FL) and programming languages (cs.PL). The mention of complexity classes such as NP and DEXPTIME suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.DS). Finally, the use of assumptions and algorithms suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and theoretical computer science in general (cs.THEORY).
